How to Apply
A cover letter is required for consideration for this position and should be attached as the first page of your resume. The cover letter should address your specific interest in the position and outline skills and experience that directly relate to this position.

Job Summary

CAEN, the IT department for the University of Michigan College of Engineering, has an excellent entry-level opportunity for recent grads or other qualified entry-level job-seekers to serve a 1-year appointment as a Linux systems administrator. You will be part of our team responsible for the installation, configuration, and remote management of the Linux systems. We provide both desktop systems used in our student computer labs and server used by our web group.

The Student Computing Environment offers students access to over a thousand Red Hat Linux desktop computers located in more than 30 locations across the Ann Arbor campus. Remote access to a pool of servers provides students with the same user experience from off campus.

Our team provides a stable and secure web hosting environment, that includes on-premise and cloud based Linux servers, to CAEN's Web Services team.

CAEN's Linux environment is run by a configuration management system that is used to deploy, update and monitor the hosts. This infrastructure uses Red Hat Enterprise Linux's native packaging system to deploy and update software.

The person chosen for this position will find themselves:
Working in an environment where they can learn and grow your skills and technical knowledge.
Involved in the debugging, troubleshooting, issue investigation, and resolution of software issues
Involved in writing documentation and communicating progress with team members and customers
May include independent research on new technologies and techniques to improve current and future systems under development
For more information about CAEN, visit: http://caen.engin.umich.edu/

Who We Are
