Responsibilities*

SYSTEM ADMINISTRATION:
Provide system administration and troubleshooting for Linux systems managed by CAEN. Customize host software configurations. Manage event logging, reporting and anomaly detection. Implement and maintain a monitoring with real time outage alerting system for CAEN managed servers and services.

OPERATING SYSTEM INTEGRATION:
Develop, maintain and distribute software images for Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL) and Ubuntu operating systems for servers, workstations, and virtual machines in a networked environment of over a thousand hosts.

SYSTEMS PROGRAMMING:
Develop and troubleshoot internal systems software. Write, maintain and document scripts in Python and other scripting languages to aid in completing recurring tasks.

LINUX SUPPORT AND CONSULTING:
Provide tier 3 end-user support to the CAEN Desktop Support group and CAEN Help Desk. Provide assistance to faculty and staff on a variety of software, hardware, network and equipment configurations. Monitor and answer support request calls and emails

DOCUMENTATION:
Provide documentation, presentations and support staff training in areas of technical responsibility. Prepare regular and ad hoc status and other reports as required by supervisor or higher level authority. Document standard methodologies.

Required Qualifications*

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or a related field, or an equivalent combination of education, certification, and experience.
1-3 years of experience administering and deploying Linux.
Experience with a Linux configuration management system Ansible, Salt, Chef or Puppet.
Experience with Linux software packaging.
Demonstrated experience with Unix shell scripting.
Proficiency with an advanced programming language, like Python, Perl or Ruby.
Ability to work effectively in a team environment and independently with minimal supervision.
Must be able to work during normal business hours with occasional work outside of normal business hours for planned upgrades and best-effort response to major outages.
Experience with writing user documentation.
Desired Qualifications*

At least 2 years experience with Red Hat Enterprise Linux.
At least 2 years experience with virtualization software such as VMWare, Oracle VirtualBox or Kernel-based Virtual Machine (KVM).
Experience with Software Configuration Management tools , preferably Git/GitHub.
Experience with networked file systems.
Experience installing and configuring Apache web servers.
Experience with automated deployment of Linux systems in a large scale environment.
Experience with cloud computing environments such as Amazon Web Services, Google Compute Environment or Microsoft Azure
Additional Information
This is a one-year term-limited appointment

Appointments made for a specified period of time are called term or term-limited appointments. The decision to appoint individuals on a term basis is often due to the funding nature of the position, or the duration of a project.

The term appointment is expected to continue for the specified period of time, assuming satisfactory conduct and performance is maintained, and funding continues as initially expected. Term appointments may be extended, or may be ended prior to the established end date. When extending appointments, the length of the extension will be clearly specified.

